headline: Has Nasdaq’s 133% Five Year Surge Left Limited Upside at $93 in 2025?
summary: If you have ever wondered whether Nasdaq at around $93 is still a buy after its long run, you are in the right place. We are going to unpack whether the current price makes sense or not. The stock has climbed 3.7% over the last week, 7.5% over the past month, and is up 20.8% year to date, building on an impressive 133.6% gain over five years that has many investors asking if the upside is already priced in.
